RUNNING THE GAME
----------------
  RootTux is made using Haxe, HaxeFlixel and Polymod.
  
  Actually, if you compile before release, Polymod and thx.core git ver
  isn't needed, as mod support won't be added until release.

  1. Install Haxe 4.3.7. Later versions that may release later will likely not work.
  2. Install HaxeFlixel 6.1.2. From the looks of it, 6.2.0, when it releases, could work, but it's best to use 6.1.2 for now.
  3. Make sure Lime and OpenFL are installed, also make sure Lime and Flixel Tools have been set up.
  4. If you're on Windows, install hscpp.
  5. If you're on Windows, install Visual Studio Community. (THIS STEP IS W.I.P, THERE ARE SPECIFIC THINGS THAT NEED TO BE INSTALLED THROUGH VISUAL STUDIO THAT AREN'T LISTED HERE)
  6. Install Polymod 1.8.0.
  7. Install thx.core from Git (You need GIt installed!) (haxelib git thx.core https://github.com/fponticelli/thx.core) (Polymod won't work without the git version of thx.core)
  8. Open the terminal in the folder the Project.xml of the game is in. You may need to use the cd command if you're on Windows.
  9. Use the command "lime test [OS] -debug", replacing [OS] with the Operating System you're using, such as windows, mac or linux. On any OS, you can compile the game to HTML5 by replacing [OS] with html5
  10. It will take more than 5 minutes to compile, so get yourself a drink and some food, watch a video or play a game.
  11. Once it's compiled, your build will be in the export folder.

PLAYING THE GAME
----------------
  Controls
  --------
  Only keyboards are supported right now. The left / A key moves Tux to
  the left, the right / D key moves Tux to the right, the space key makes
  Tux jump, the down / S key makes Tux duck, the left CTRL (Control) /
  left shift key makes Tux shoot fire if he's got the fire power-up.


